{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "For the training dataset, we randomly sampled 700 notes for each of the five selected clinical entities.",
    "We only sampled notes that the CheXpert agent labeled as \"present\" or \"negated\" to upsample notes with information relevant to our retrieval task.",
    "We used a similar approach for the testing dataset, sampling 200 notes per entity, 100 of which had been labeled by CheXpert as \"present\" and 100 as \"negated\".",
    "After selection, CheXpert labels were discarded for both datasets.",
    "In total, we had 3500 patients containing 3500 unique notes in the testing dataset, and 1000 patients containing 1000 unique notes in the training dataset."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}